{{Refimprove|date=February 2015}} {{Infobox company | name = CMD Group | logo = [[File:CMD Group Logo.png|250px|CMD Group provides construction market data and construction leads]] | logo_size = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_padding = | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = <!-- Use ISO 639-1 code, e.g. "fr" for French. For multiple names in different languages, use {{lang|[code]|[name]}}. --> | former_name = Construction Market Data, Reed Construction Data | type = [[Publishing company]] | industry = [[Construction]] | founded = 1982 | founder = <!-- or: | founders = --> | hq_location = 30 Technology Parkway South, Suite 100 | hq_location_city = [[Peachtree Corners, Georgia]] | hq_location_country = [[United States]] | area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = --> | key_people = | products = | brands = | services = construction market data, construction leads | owners = [[Warburg Pincus]], [[Reed Elsevier]] | homepage = {{URL|CMDgroup.com}} }} '''CMD Group''', formerly Reed Construction Data and Construction Market Data, is a provider of [[business information]] for the [[North America]]n construction industry. CMD is owned by [[Warburg Pincus]] (51%) and [[Reed Business Information]] (49%). Its historical roots lie in Construction Market Data, founded in 1982 to publish construction leads and market data. In 2000, London-based [[Reed Elsevier]] purchased this original CMD Group, transitioning the company to Reed Construction Data.
In October 2014 [[private equity firm]] Warburg Pincus in New York purchased a majority stake in the company, and Reed Construction Data changed its name to CMD.<ref>http://www.hconews.com/articles/2014/10/8/reed-construction-data-rebrands-cmd</ref> The Norcross, Ga.-based provider of North American construction data said the new name is a nod to the company’s original name: Construction Market Data. The new brand includes an updated logo and website.<ref>http://www.bizjournals.com/atlanta/news/2014/10/01/reed-construction-data-rebrands-itself-as-cmd.html</ref>
The company tracks data on hundreds of thousands of projects per year, providing coverage of construction projects in both the United States and Canada. The company provides monthly analysis and data for all aspects of the construction industry. CMD also provides a detailed view of construction activity, including historical data, current-year projections and a five-year forecast. Their research helps customers forecast to find those market segments experiencing the greatest growth and plan tactical marketing strategies.<ref>http://www.hconews.com/articles/2014/10/8/reed-construction-data-rebrands-cmd</ref>
==Lawsuits== In October 2009, Reed Construction Data (which is now Construction Market Data a division of ConstructCONNECT) filed suit in [[United States district court|federal court]] against [[McGraw-Hill Construction]], charging that the company's Dodge Report had unlawfully accessed confidential and trade secret information from Reed since 2002 by using a series of fake companies to pose as Reed customers. The lawsuit, filed in the [[U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York]], seeks an unspecified amount in lost profits and punitive damages, trial by jury, and injunctive relief as a result of Dodge’s misuse of proprietary construction project information, and that Dodge allegedly manipulated the information to create misleading comparisons between Dodge’s and Reed’s products and services in an effort to mislead the marketplace.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reedconstructiondata.com/corporate/press-releases/2009/10/reed-construction-data-files-corporate-espionage-lawsuit-against-mcgraw-hil |title=Reed Construction Data Files Corporate Espionage Lawsuit Against McGraw-Hill Construction Dodge |publisher=Reedconstructiondata.com |date=2009-10-08 |accessdate=2013-10-02}}</ref>{{when|date=March 2013}}
==Merger==
In 2016, CMD Group became a part of ConstructConnect as part of a merger with [[iSqFt]], BidClerk, [[Construction Data Company|Construction Data]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/news/2016/05/13/fast-growing-isqft-combines-with-3-firms-to-form.html|title=iSqFt combines with 3 firms to form ConstructConnect - Cincinnati Business Courier|website=Cincinnati Business Courier|access-date=2016-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/DJFLBO0120150804eb84ipzwd|title=Warburg's CMD to Merge With Genstar-Backed iSqFt|date=2015-08-04|newspaper=Wall Street Journal|issn=0099-9660|access-date=2016-06-20}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bizjournals.com/cincinnati/news/2015/08/04/fast-growing-isqft-merges-with-construction-data.html|title=iSqFt merges with construction data firm - Cincinnati Business Courier|website=Cincinnati Business Courier|access-date=2016-06-20}}</ref>
